{:metadata {:description [{"text" "<p>This family includes two functionally redundant pectin methyltransferases, Cotton Golgi-related 2 and 3 (CGR2/3), which are required for homogalacturonan pectins (HG) methylesterification in the Golgi apparatus prior to integration into cell walls, essential for general growth and development [[cite:PUB00096844], [cite:PUB00096845]]. Changes in pectin composition impacts carbon (C) partitioning, photosynthesis and respiration efficiency by influencing leaf mesophyll cell walls morphology and physiology. Pectin methylesterification modulates both expansion and positioning of cells in leaves, probably by changing cell walls plasticity [[cite:PUB00096845]].</p>", "llm" false, "checked" false, "updated" false}], :is-reviewed-llm false, :representative-structure nil, :overlaps-with [{"accession" "IPR029063", "name" "S-adenosyl-L-methionine-dependent methyltransferase superfamily", "type" "homologous_superfamily"}], :member-databases {"panther" {"PTHR34208" "S-ADENOSYL-L-METHIONINE-DEPENDENT METHYLTRANSFERASE-RELATED"}}, :is-updated-llm false, :name {"name" "Pectin methyltransferase CGR2/3", "short" "CGR2/3"}, :wikipedia nil, :source-database "interpro", :type "family", :counters {"structures" 0, "domain_architectures" 0, "proteomes" 244, "taxa" 978, "subfamilies" 0, "interactions" 0, "matches" 1391, "sets" 0, "proteins" 1391, "structural_models" {"alphafold" 822}, "pathways" 145}, :integrated nil, :cross-references {"ec" {"displayName" "ENZYME", "description" "ENZYME is a repository of information relative to the nomenclature of enzymes. It is primarily based on the recommendations of the Nomenclature Committee of the International Union of Biochemistry and Molecular Biology (IUBMB) and it describes each type of characterized enzyme for which an EC (Enzyme Commission) number has been provided.", "rank" 19, "accessions" [{"accession" "2.1.1.-", "url" "https://enzyme.expasy.org/EC/2.1.1.-"}]}}, :set-info nil, :accession "IPR044689", :l